quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  55,26,"All that (exists) upon it (i.e., the earth) is vanishing"
  55,27,"And there (still) remains (forever) The Face of your Lord, The Owner of Majesty and Munificence"
  55,28,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,29,Whoever are in the heavens and the earth ask Him; every Day He is upon some (momentous) affair
  55,30,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,31,"We will soon finish your (affair), O you (both) overburdened (Or: discomforted) ones! (i.e., the jinn and humankind (see verse)"
  55,32,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,33,"O company of the jinn and humankind, in case you are able to penetrate through the regions of the heavens and the earth, then penetrate (them)! You will not penetrate except with an all-binding authority"
  55,34,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,35,"Against you (both) will be sent flares of fire, and (molten) brass; then you will not vindicate yourselves"
  55,36,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,37,"Then, when the heaven is cloven so it becomes rosy-like ointment"
  55,38,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,39,Then upon that Day neither any of humankind nor any of the jinn (race) will be questioned about his guilty deed
  55,40,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,41,"The criminals will be recognized by their marks, and (they) will be taken (away) by (their) forelocks and (their) feet"
  55,42,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,43,This is Hell to which criminals cry lies
  55,44,"They go round between it and between duly boiling (Or: hot) scalding water"
  55,45,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies